{
  "stem": "293.1",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "You're losing the arm for fighting for-- for Poland.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Poland will never forget you.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "When you give me order to amputate the arm, I will obey.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "I give him the order.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "The hand was amputated.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "The boy survived, and strange things-- I got a-- I have it here, a letter from a Polish nurse from Poland that-- because they found out I put an ad in the paper that I'm looking for my orderly-- that he lives someplace around the [NON-ENGLISH], that I should contact the [? competent ?] organization of Poland.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "They will find him for me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "I didn't have the time, but this came about a month ago.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "So I have still time to look it for him.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he was one of the very rare Jews that was fighting the Germans before--",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There were lots of Jews fighting the Germans in Polish Army, quite a bit.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Soldiers and officers.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were other Jewish officers, doctors, and-- and-- trained professional, even professional Jewish officer were there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My life was completely changed because I was destined to do something else.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But on account of the war, my whole education, my whole talent was wasted-- [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On the-- on the end of the war?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- I was taken prisoner of war because I was in city of [NON-ENGLISH], and the German-- because remember, we are under jurisdiction of the army, not the Gestapo or SS.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The army control.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They give us a choice to the officer-- they didn't ask that I'm Jewish or not Jewish-- that we can go to the prisoner of war to Russia because they were-- Russia were taking back this part of the river [NON-ENGLISH] from Germany.",
      "word_count": 43
    }
  ],
